	ThaiLin Semiconductor Corp. (ThaiLin).


	ThaiLin was incorporated in Taiwan in May 1996 and is listed
	on the GreTai Securities Market in Taiwan. It is engaged in providing semiconductor testing services.




	We have an indirect interest in
	ThaiLin. As of September 30, 2012, ChipMOS TECHNOLOGIES INC., or ChipMOS Taiwan, our 84.2% owned subsidiary held 104.7 million shares of ThaiLin, comprising 42.9% of the outstanding shares in ThaiLin (which does not include 11 million
	shares of ThaiLin pledged to ChipMOS Taiwan by another shareholder of ThaiLin). These shares were primarily acquired by ChipMOS Taiwan in December 2002. Under applicable accounting principles, ThaiLin was consolidated into our consolidated financial
	statements in 2003 because ChipMOS Taiwan was deemed to exert significant control over ThaiLin through common directors and management. Mr. Shih-Jye Cheng, our chairman and chief executive officer and the director and chairman of ChipMOS
	Taiwan, is also a director and the chairman of ThaiLin. In addition, four of the nine directors of ThaiLin are appointed by ChipMOS Taiwan.




	As of September 30, 2012, ThaiLin held 6,474,211 of our issued and outstanding common shares, corresponding to 19.1% of all of our issued and
	outstanding common shares. ThaiLins current holding includes 1,015,158 shares acquired in 2009 pursuant to ThaiLins enforcement of its rights under a stock pledge agreement with another shareholder; 506,364 shares accumulated from
	purchases under a Rule 10b5-1/10b-18 securities purchase program during December 2008 to August 2009; and 4,952,689 shares acquired in 2010 and 2011 pursuant to convertible notes issued by us to ThaiLin in 2009.






